column5: Was out for about an hr and half this evening. Managed 2 33"ers, and a 30" in the span of 15 mins in 6 casts LOL! Never had a roll quite like that before.  My net had a small hole in the bottom already from cutting a lure out a while ago, the first pike when I got him into the boat fell through the net and made the hole much larger, so the next 2 pike I had to grab by hand. Guess I need a new net.
Nice work brother! Glad to see youre on them simcoe gators! Im hoping to get out next weekend.
Well done, great avatar pic  too!
Managed 2 33"ers, and a 30" in the span of 15 mins in 6 casts LOL! Never had a roll quite like that before.    Some days the fishing gods just smile on us LOL
nice grab.  I'm looking at going up there this Thursday and to rent a boat for 1/2 day.  Any suggestions?
Let me know if you ever want someone to hold the camera for you!!!!  I'm just up the rd in Barrie!  Dangerous out there alone eh..
Sounds like a great flurry ! I don't use nets. I don't like the way they roll around and get all tangled in the line and net. Hand landing is the way to go
Nice going.  You sure have got them figured out based on your last 2 reports !
Thanks, Ya I've always made out fairly well out there
